                    <span>Beat Generation poetry.  Obscene and profane, but is it great?
<br />
<br />This book is introduced by Williams Carlos Williams, a far better poet, who really should have known better than to pass Ginsberg's rants off as poetry.
<br />
<br />There is energy and youth evident in Howl, but there is also an abundance of hogwash and lies. </span>
                  
